<p>The SCP Wiki has many resources to help you get feedback, and articles that have been critiqued are far more likely to be successful, despite the fact that some threads go unnoticed and lack constructive criticism, only to die a lonely death in the darkness of the void. Still, it is the best interest of those of the Foundation and subsequent archivists that you post finiashed materiels[sic].</p>
